---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Projects & Initiatives - Dr. Venkatapathy Subramanian"
  description="Leadership roles and initiatives in AI and education"
>
  <h1>Projects & Initiatives</h1>
  
  <p class="lead">
    Beyond research, I have led several initiatives focused on bringing AI technologies to underserved communities, 
    integrating traditional knowledge systems into education, and building capacity in AI across India.
  </p>

  <section id="anaadi">
    <h2 class="section-title">Anaadi Rural AI Center</h2>
    <div class="featured-project">
      <div class="project-header">
        <div>
          <h3>Director & Co-Founder</h3>
          <div class="project-meta">2020 - July 2025 • Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu</div>
        </div>
        <div class="project-logo">
          <img src="/images/anaadi-logo.png" alt="Anaadi Foundation" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p>
        Anaadi (ஆனாதி - "that which has no beginning") was a rural AI center I founded and directed, dedicated to democratizing 
        access to artificial intelligence technologies and preserving Indian Knowledge Systems through 
        computational methods.
      </p>

      <h4>Mission</h4>
      <p>
        To bridge the digital divide by bringing AI education and applications to rural communities, 
        while using AI as a tool to preserve and extend traditional knowledge systems.
      </p>

      <h4>Key Programs</h4>
      
      <div class="program">
        <h5>AI Education for Rural Youth</h5>
        <p>
          Free training programs in machine learning, data science, and AI fundamentals for students 
          from rural backgrounds. Over 500 students trained since 2020.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>6-month intensive bootcamp in AI/ML</li>
          <li>Scholarship support for underprivileged students</li>
          <li>Mentorship and placement assistance</li>
          <li>Courses delivered in Tamil and English</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="program">
        <h5>AI for Agriculture</h5>
        <p>
          Practical AI applications for local farmers, including crop disease detection, yield prediction, 
          and market price forecasting.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Mobile app for crop disease identification (10,000+ active users)</li>
          <li>Soil health assessment using ML</li>
          <li>Weather prediction models for local microclimates</li>
          <li>Integration with traditional farming knowledge</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="program">
        <h5>Digital Heritage Lab</h5>
        <p>
          Digitization and computational analysis of Tamil manuscripts, inscriptions, and oral traditions.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Digitized 2,000+ palm leaf manuscripts</li>
          <li>OCR pipeline for historical Tamil scripts</li>
          <li>Oral history recording and transcription project (200+ hours)</li>
          <li>Collaboration with temples, libraries, and private collectors</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="program">
        <h5>Organic Farming & Cow Conservation</h5>
        <p>
          Research on indigenous cow breeds and traditional organic farming methods, integrated with 
          modern agricultural technology.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>20-acre organic farm demonstrating traditional techniques</li>
          <li>Conservation program for native Tamil Nadu cow breeds</li>
          <li>Data collection on traditional farming practices</li>
          <li>AI-powered optimization of traditional methods</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h4>Impact</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>500+</strong> students trained in AI/ML</li>
        <li><strong>10,000+</strong> farmers using our mobile applications</li>
        <li><strong>2,000+</strong> manuscripts digitized</li>
        <li><strong>50+</strong> research publications and projects by our students</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="project-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/AnaadiAI" target="_blank">GitHub</a> • 
        <a href="#">Website</a> • 
        <a href="#">Donate</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="aicte-iks">
    <h2 class="section-title">AICTE IKS Division</h2>
    <div class="featured-project">
      <h3>Consultant</h3>
      <div class="project-meta">2022 - Present • All India Council for Technical Education</div>
      
      <p>
        As a consultant to AICTE's Indian Knowledge Systems (IKS) Division, I work on integrating 
        traditional Indian knowledge into modern technical education curricula across engineering and 
        technology institutions in India.
      </p>

      <h4>Key Responsibilities</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Curriculum development for IKS-Tech integration courses</li>
        <li>Faculty training programs on teaching IKS concepts</li>
        <li>Evaluation of IKS research proposals and projects</li>
        <li>Policy recommendations for IKS integration in technical education</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Initiatives</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Developed course modules on "AI for Indian Knowledge Systems" (adopted by 100+ institutions)</li>
        <li>Organized national-level workshops for faculty (2,000+ participants)</li>
        <li>Created resource repository of IKS-Tech learning materials</li>
        <li>Established research grant program for IKS-Tech projects (₹5 crore allocated)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="atal">
    <h2 class="section-title">Atal Innovation Mission</h2>
    <div class="featured-project">
      <h3>Regional Mentor of Change</h3>
      <div class="project-meta">2019 - 2022 • NITI Aayog, Government of India</div>
      
      <p>
        As an Atal Regional Mentor of Change, I guided innovation and entrepreneurship activities in 
        schools and higher education institutions across Tamil Nadu and Kerala from 2019 to 2022.
      </p>

      <h4>Activities</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Mentoring 50+ Atal Tinkering Labs (ATLs) in schools</li>
        <li>Organizing hackathons and innovation challenges</li>
        <li>Providing technical guidance on AI/ML projects</li>
        <li>Connecting student innovators with industry and research institutions</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Notable Student Projects Mentored</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>AI-powered assistive device for visually impaired students (won national award)</li>
        <li>Water quality monitoring system using IoT and ML</li>
        <li>Tamil language learning app using speech recognition</li>
        <li>Low-cost agricultural robots for small farmers</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="other-initiatives">
    <h2 class="section-title">Other Initiatives & Affiliations</h2>

    <div class="initiative-grid">
      <div class="initiative-card">
        <h3>Open Sanskrit Initiative</h3>
        <p class="role">Advisory Board Member</p>
        <p>
          Supporting open-source tools and datasets for Sanskrit NLP, including tokenizers, 
          morphological analyzers, and digital libraries.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="initiative-card">
        <h3>Indic NLP Researchers Network</h3>
        <p class="role">Founder & Organizer</p>
        <p>
          Community of 300+ researchers working on NLP for Indian languages. Organizes monthly 
          seminars and annual conferences.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="initiative-card">
        <h3>Tamil Computing Conference</h3>
        <p class="role">Organizing Committee</p>
        <p>
          Annual conference bringing together researchers, developers, and enthusiasts working on 
          Tamil language technology.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="initiative-card">
        <h3>AI Ethics Working Group</h3>
        <p class="role">Member</p>
        <p>
          Policy working group advising on ethical use of AI in cultural heritage digitization 
          and indigenous knowledge systems.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="initiative-card">
        <h3>Google Summer of Code</h3>
        <p class="role">Mentor</p>
        <p>
          Mentoring students on open-source projects related to Indic languages and digital humanities 
          since 2021.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="initiative-card">
        <h3>Digital Library of India</h3>
        <p class="role">Technical Advisor</p>
        <p>
          Advising on AI/ML applications for cataloging, search, and access to digitized Indian texts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="awards">
    <h2 class="section-title">Awards & Recognition</h2>
    <ul class="awards-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Best Paper Award</strong> - International Conference on Document Analysis and Recognition (ICDAR), 2023
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>AICTE IKS Excellence Award</strong> - For outstanding contribution to IKS-Tech integration, 2023
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Tamil Computing Pioneer Award</strong> - Tamil Internet Conference, 2022
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Social Impact Fellowship</strong> - Ashoka University, 2021
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Emerging Leader in AI</strong> - ACM India, 2020
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="collaborations">
    <h2 class="section-title">Collaborations Welcome</h2>
    <p>
      I'm always interested in collaborating with researchers, institutions, and organizations working 
      at the intersection of AI and social good, particularly in areas related to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Indic language technologies and low-resource NLP</li>
      <li>Digital preservation of cultural heritage</li>
      <li>AI for education and rural development</li>
      <li>Ethical AI and technology for social impact</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If you're interested in partnering with Anaadi or collaborating on research, please 
      <a href="/#contact">get in touch</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  ul {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .featured-project {
    background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .project-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .featured-project h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .featured-project h4 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .featured-project h5 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .project-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .project-logo img {
    max-width: 100px;
    height: auto;
  }

  .program {
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .program h5 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .project-links {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .project-links a {
    margin-right: 1rem;
  }

  .initiative-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .initiative-card {
    background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .initiative-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .initiative-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .role {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .initiative-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .awards-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .awards-list li {
    padding: 1rem;
    background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project-header {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .project-logo {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>

